<inglise> Council Directive 75/271/EEC of 28 April 1975 concerning the Community list of less-favoured farming areas within the meaning of Directive No 75/268/EEC (France) </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu direktiiv 75/271/EM&Uuml;, milles k&auml;sitletakse loetelu &uuml;henduse ebasoodsamate p&otilde;llumajanduspiirkondade kohta direktiivis 75/268/EM&Uuml; m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses (Prantsusmaa) 28. aprill 1975 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive No 75/268/EEC (1) of 28 April 1975 on mountain and hill farming in certain less-favoured areas, and in particular Article 2 (2) thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 28. aprilli 1975. aasta direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml;m&auml;gipiirkondade ja teatavate ebasoodsamate piirkondade p&otilde;llumajanduse kohta, (1) eriti selle artikli 2 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the European Parliament; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2); </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Government of the French Republic communicated to the Commission, in accordance with Article 2 (1) of Directive No 75/268/EEC, the areas which, within the meaning of Article 3 (3) of the said Directive, are suitable for inclusion in the Community list of less-favoured farming areas and the information concerning the characteristics of these areas; whereas the information relating to those areas located in the overseas departments is not sufficiently complete to enable the Commission to give its view on them at present; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Prantsuse Vabariigi valitsus on teatanud komisjonile vastavalt direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 2 l&otilde;ikele 1 piirkonnad, mis k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 3 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses sobivad &uuml;henduse ebasoodsamate p&otilde;llumajanduspiirkondade loetelusse, ning andmed nende piirkondade ise&auml;rasuste kohta; teave k&otilde;nealuste &uuml;lemeredepartemangudes asuvate piirkondade kohta ei ole piisavalt p&otilde;hjalik, et komisjonil oleks v&otilde;imalik praegu nende kohta hinnangut anda; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the index used for defining very difficult climatic conditions in accordance with the first indent of Article 3 (3) of Directive No 75/268/EEC, was a minimum altitude of 600 m over at least 80 % of the surface of the territory of each commune, and not only for the major part thereof; whereas, moreover, the division of communes is not recognized, and whereas the minimum altitude fixed can therefore be considered, with regard to the Directive, as being between 600 and 700 m; </inglise>
<eesti> v&auml;ga raskete ilmastikutingimuste m&auml;&auml;ramiseks vastavalt direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 3 esimesele taandele on kasutatud indeksit, mille puhul on minimaalne k&otilde;rgus merepinnast 600 m v&auml;hemalt 80% ulatuses iga kommuuni territooriumist ja mitte ainult suuremal osal kommuunist; kommuunide jaotust ei tunnustata ning k&otilde;nealust direktiivi arvesse v&otilde;ttes saab minimaalse k&otilde;rgusena merepinnast k&auml;sitada 600-700 m; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the index used to define steep slopes, according to Article 3 (3), second indent of Directive No 75/268/EEC, was a difference in level of at least 400 m between the highest and lowest points of the utilized agricultural area of the commune; whereas a detailed examination has been made by the Commission on the basis, mainly, of a study of slopes per square kilometre (20 % and greater), aimed at removing the uncertainties resulting from the abovementioned index of differences in level; whereas this examination also took into account the possibility opened up by Article 3 (3), third indent of Directive No 75/268/EEC, of combining the two factors: altitude and slope, if this combination resulted in the same total handicap; whereas it is therefore possible to state that only a very limited number of communes on the fringes of the communicated mountain areas do not fully comply with the required conditions, but that they nevertheless comply with those of Article 3 (4) of the said Directive; whereas since their economies are closely bound up with that of bordering communes, they can nevertheless be classed as mountain areas; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 3 teisele taandele on j&auml;rskude n&otilde;lvade m&auml;&auml;ratlemise indeksina kasutatud kommuunis p&otilde;llumajandusliku k&otilde;lviku k&otilde;ige k&otilde;rgemate ja madalamate punktide vahet v&auml;hemalt 400 m; peamiselt uurimuse p&otilde;hjal, milles k&auml;sitletakse n&otilde;lvu &uuml;he ruutkilomeetri kohta (20% ja enam) viis komisjon l&auml;bi &uuml;ksikasjaliku uuringu, et k&otilde;rvaldada eespool nimetatud k&otilde;rgusevahe indeksist tulenevad ebaselgused; nimetatud uuringu k&auml;igus v&otilde;eti arvesse direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 3 kolmandas taandes esitatud v&otilde;imalust siduda kahte faktorit, k&otilde;rgust ja kallakut, kui nende sidumise tulemuseks on sama ebasoodsad olud; seet&otilde;ttu v&otilde;ib v&auml;ita, et ainult v&auml;ga v&auml;hesed nimetatud m&auml;gipiirkondade piirialadel asuvad kommuunid ei vasta n&otilde;utud tingimustele t&auml;ielikult, kuid vastavad siiski nimetatud direktiivi artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud tingimustele; kuna nende majandus on tihedalt seotud piiri&auml;&auml;rsete kommuunide majandusega, on neid siiski v&otilde;imalik m&auml;gipiirkondadena klassifitseerida; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in these conditions, the nature and level of the abovementioned indices, utilized by the Government of the French Republic to define the areas communicated to the Commission, conform to the characteristics of mountain areas according to Article 3 (3) of Directive No 75/268/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> nendel tingimustel vastab Prantsuse Vabariigi valitsuse poolt komisjonile teatatud piirkondade m&auml;&auml;ratlemiseks kasutatavate eespool nimetatud n&auml;itajate olemus ja tase vastavalt direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele 3 m&auml;gipiirkondade kirjeldusele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the communication of the Member State concerned fails to indicate the present situation in these areas, from the point of view of infrastructure according to Article 3 (2) of the said Directive, whereas it seems that the infrastructure is not always adequate; whereas the absence of information on current or proposed programmes makes it impossible to estimate the time which will be taken to achieve an improvement in this position; whereas it nevertheless seems expedient to include the areas in question in the Community list of less-favoured farming areas, on the understanding that the Government of the French Republic will shortly submit to the Commission a detailed communication on this subject, </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud infrastruktuuri silmas pidades ei n&auml;ita asjaomase liikmesriigi teatis praegust olukorda nendes piirkondades, seega tundub, et infrastruktuur ei ole alati piisav; kuna puudub teave j&otilde;ustunud v&otilde;i kavandatavate programmide kohta, ei ole v&otilde;imalik hinnata, kui palju aega selles k&uuml;simuses edusammude saavutamiseks kulub; siiski tundub otstarbekas lisada k&otilde;nealused alad &uuml;henduse ebasoodsamate p&otilde;llumajanduspiirkondade loetelusse eeldusel, et Prantsuse Vabariigi valitsus esitab l&auml;hiajal komisjonile selle kohta &uuml;ksikasjaliku teatise, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The Member State concerned will forward to the Commission by the end of 1975 at the latest, a detailed communication indicating the time within which measures for the substantial improvement of this infrastructure will be effective in the areas referred to in Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Asjaomane liikmesriik edastab komisjonile hiljemalt 1975. aasta l&otilde;puks &uuml;ksikasjaliku teatise t&auml;htaja kohta, mille jooksul kehtivad artiklis 1 osutatud aladel selle infrastruktuuri oluliseks parandamiseks etten&auml;htud meetmed. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive is addressed to the French Republic. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv on adresseeritud Prantsuse Vabariigile. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 28 April 1975. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 28. august 1975 N&otilde;ukogu nimel </eesti>
